order to produce the most objective reviews possible.\\n\\n### Office Work\\n\\nOffice Work should be used mostly by users who spend most of the time looking at pieces of text, tables or just surfing.\\nThis profile aims to deliver better distinctness and clarity by keeping a flat gamma curve (2.20), native color temperature and perceptually accurate colors.\\n\\n* $9.90 BUY NOW\\n\\n### Design and Gaming\\n\\nThis profile is aimed at designers who work with colors professionally, and for games and movies as well. Design and Gaming takes display panels to their limits, making them as accurate as possible in the sRGB IEC61966-2-1 standard for Web and HDTV, at white point D65.\\n\\n* $9.90 BUY NOW\\n\\n### Health-Guard\\n\\nHealth-Guard eliminates the [harmful Pulse-Width Modulation](http://laptopmedia.com/highlights/what-is-pwm-why-is-it-important-and-why-did-we-add-this-test-to-our-reviews/) (PWM) and reduces the [negative Blue Light](http://laptopmedia.com/reviews/health-impact-of-display-blue-light-and-our-solutions-for-you/) which affects our eyes and body. Since it’s custom tailored for every panel, it manages to keep the colors perceptually accurate.\\nHealth-Guard simulates paper so the pressure on the eyes is greatly reduced.\\n\\n* $9.90 BUY NOW\\n\\n## Get all 3 profiles with 33% discount\\n\\n* $19.90 BUY NOW\\n\\n## CPU performance\\n\\nHere you can find the price/performance difference between all the CPUs that come in the HP OMEN 15 (15-ek0000, ek1000) series.\\n\\n3D Rendering\\n\\n## Here, we evaluate the CPU's performance using a real-world 3D rendering task, assessing its ability to handle complex computations and rendering workloads efficiently.\\n\\n#### Results are from the Cinebench 2024 Multi-Core test (higher is better)\\n\\n[Intel Core i5-10300H](https://laptopmedia.com/processor/intel-core-i5-10300h/) [HP OMEN 15](https://laptopmedia.com/laptop-specs/hp-omen-gaming-laptop-15t-ek000-38/)\\n\\n[331](https://www.awin1.com/pclick.php?p=26998896393&a=568859&m=7168)\\n\\n[Intel Core i7-11800H](https://laptopmedia.com/processor/intel-core-i7-11800h/) [HP OMEN 15](https://laptopmedia.com/laptop-specs/hp-omen-15-1617/)\\n\\n[582](https://www.amazon.\\ncom/exec/obidos/ASIN/B0B628JHZP?tag=specslaptops-20&linkCode=assoc-rails-rate-card-link-code-tw3)\\n\\n[Intel Core i5-11400H](https://laptopmedia.com/processor/intel-core-i5-11400h/) [HP OMEN 15](https://laptopmedia.com/laptop-specs/hp-omen-gaming-laptop-15t-ek100-73/)\\n\\n[414](https://www.awin1.com/pclick.php?p=31316653009&a=568859&m=7168)\\n\\n## GPU performance\\n\\nHere you can find the price/performance difference between all the GPUs that come in the HP OMEN 15 (15-ek0000, ek1000) series.\\n\\n## HP OMEN 15 (15-ek0000, ek1000) in-depth review\\n\\nEver since 2017, HP has used pretty much the same design for their Omen series. Indeed it was a fresh new feature back then, but quite honestly, it looked a bit too aggressive. Fast-forward to 2020, and we see that HP has taken some notes from Lenovo and their Legion series, which are one of the most incognito gaming notebooks on the market.However, looks are not the only difference we see.\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.blisscomputers.net/hp-omen-15-ce0xx-lcd-screen-15-6-1920x1080-laptop-display-331487\",\n      \"title\": \"description: Low Prices. Fast Shipping. 25 Years in Screen Industry Experience. Buy Online With Confidence! HP omen 15-ce0xx LCD Screen 15.6\\\" 1920x1080 laptop Display. title: HP omen 15-ce0xx LCD Screen 15.6\\\" 1920x1080 laptop Display image: https://cdn11.bigcommerce.com/s-vy9cg/products/566407/images/91347348/11895__13603.1777743224.380.500.jpg?c=2\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"---\\ndescription: Low Prices. Fast Shipping. 25 Years in Screen Industry Experience. Buy Online With Confidence! HP omen 15-ce0xx LCD Screen 15.6&quot; 1920x1080 laptop Display.\\ntitle: HP omen 15-ce0xx LCD Screen 15.6&quot; 1920x1080 laptop Displa