l,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"# Laptop Repairability Scores\\n\\nJump to Scores\\n\\n# You have the right to repair the things you own—but how easily can that be done?\\n\\nTo find out, our engineers tear down the latest laptops and score their repairability from zero (unrepairable) to ten (easiest to repair) so you can pick a product that is easy to repair and lasts as long as possible.\\n\\n# What makes a repairable device?\\n\\nIt should be straightforward to disassemble and replace whatever’s broken, using parts and instructions supplied (or endorsed) by the manufacturer. But that’s just to start—repairability means so much more. For full details, see our [repairability scoring explainer](https://www.ifixit.com/News/75533/how-ifixit-scores-repairability) .\\n\\n# Repairability is a moving target\\n\\nWe update our scoring rubric frequently to stay current with new technologies, materials, and design trends.\\nThis means that devices scored in years past might not fare exactly the same if they were re-scored today, but they can be readily compared with their contemporaries. For a precise list of criteria used to calculate each score, click the scorecard version number linked to each device below. For a downloadable (CSV) list of all scores, [click here](https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1R_egXm7iwR0isCt_UxcGtheFEwLj9SNhxC5DWnAqKIc/edit=0) .\\n\\n* * *\\n\\n# Laptop Scores\\n\\nSorted by newest to oldest\\n\\n# Lenovo ThinkPad T14 Gen 7 and T16 Gen 5\\n\\n2026\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Storage and memory are readily repairable/upgradeable using industry-standard parts.\\n* The battery is easily replaced, and the keyboard replacement procedure is best-in-class.\\n* Overall very high modularity, including individually replaceable Thunderbolt ports.\\n* Lenovo provides thorough repair instructions and sells replacement parts.\\n\\n[Scorecard v2.2](https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v2.2)\\n# MacBook Pro 14-inch (M5, 2025)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/MacBook_Pro_14%22_2025_%28M5%29)\\n\\n2025\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Battery replacements are do-able (if not exactly easy).\\n* The Thunderbolt port design is highly modular and repair-friendly.\\n* Apple offers a full service manual and a good selection of replacement parts for end users.\\n\\n###### CONS\\n\\n* Storage is not removable or serviceable, the keyboard is riveted down, and pentalobe screws bar the way for all repairs.\\n\\n[Scorecard v2.2](https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v2.2)\\n\\n# Lenovo ThinkPad P16 Gen 3\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Lenovo_ThinkPad_P16_Gen_3)\\n\\n2025\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Storage and memory are readily repairable/upgradeable using industry-standard parts.\\n* The battery is easily replaced, and the keyboard replacement procedure is best-in-class.\\n* Lenovo typically provides thorough support for P-series repairs (instructions and replacement parts).\\n\\n###### CONS\\n\\n...\\n\\n# MacBook Air 15″ (M2)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/MacBook_Air_15%22_2023)\\n\\n2023\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Battery repairs are tough but do-able, and the fanless design is low-maintenance.\\n* Apple offers full repair instructions and replacement parts for end users.\\n\\n###### CONS\\n\\n* Storage is soldered, the keyboard is riveted down, and pentalobe screws bar the way for all repairs.\\n\\n[Scorecard v1.6](https://www.ifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v1.6)  \\n**[Learn More](https://www.ifixit.com/News/62674/m2-macbook-air-teardown-apple-forgot-the-heatsink)**\\n\\n# MacBook Air 13″ (M2)\\n\\n[](https://www.ifixit.com/Device/Macbook_Air_M2_2022)\\n\\n2022\\n\\n###### PROS\\n\\n* Battery repairs are tough but do-able, and the fanless design is low-maintenance.\\n* Apple offers full repair instructions and replacement parts for end users.\\n\\n###### CONS\\n\\n* Storage is soldered, the keyboard is riveted down, and pentalobe screws bar the way for all repairs.\\n\\n[Scorecard v1.6](https://www.ifixit.\\n\\n...\\n\\nifixit.com/Wiki/Repairability_Scoring_Rubric_v1.3)  \\n**[Learn More](https://www.ifixit.com/News/54122/macbook-pro-2021-teardown)**\\n\\n[View Legacy Scores](https://www.ifixit.com/repairability/legacy-laptop-scores)\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/Device/HP_Pavilion_15\",\n      \"title\": \"HP Pavilion 15 Series Repair Help: Learn How to Fix It Yourself. - iFixit\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Free Shipping on Domestic Orders $75+\\n\\nHP Pavilion 15 Series\\n\\nTable of Contents\\n\\n* Background\\n* Identification\\n* Additional Information\\n\\n* Edit\\n* Options\\n\\n* History\\n* \\n* Show Other Languages\\n\\nHP Pavilion 15 Series\\n\\n# HP Pavilion 15 Series Repair\\n\\nDevice repair and information for HP's line of Pavilion 15\\\" laptop computers.\\n\\nAuthor: Jeff Stephens (and 7 other contributors)\\n\\nCreate a Guide\\n\\n## Popular Forum Questions\\n\\nAsk a Question\\n\\n|3 Answers\\n\\n10 Score |### How to solve 5 long and 3 short caps lock blink? and not turning on. It shows 5 long and 3 short caps lock blink error....\\\")\\n\\nHP Pavilion 15 Series |\\n| --- | --- |\\n|2 Answers\\n\\n0 Score |### HP Pavilion 15 -- Verification of flashed BIOS image failed bootloop\\n\\nHP Pavilion 15 Series |\\n|1 Answer\\n\\n2 Score |### re-attaching a bezel to laptop screen\\n\\nHP Pavilion 15 Series |\\n|1 Answer\\n\\n0 Score |### Bios update corrupted but I try to recover it but its not working\\n\\nHP Pavilion 15-cc561st |\\n\\n## Background\\nHP Pavilion computers have existed since 1995. They generally compete with similar lines from Toshiba and Acer. For many people, 15 inch laptops hit the ‘Goldilocks zone’ of laptops. They’re not too big or small, and they have enough space for a good processor without sacrificing portability. These laptops are popular with content creators and professionals who need to be productive and do occasional creative tasks, but also want a reasonably portable laptop.\\n\\n## Identification\\n\\nMost HP Pavilion 15 model numbers begin with 15-, and use 15.6\\\" screens. To find your exact model of HP Pavilion 15, look for the serial number and/or the model or product number. This is often on the bottom or side of the laptop, or in the battery compartment if it is removable.\\n\\nThis [HP page](https://www.hp.com/us-en/shop/tech-takes/how-to-find-hp-laptop-model-number) explains in more detail how to find these identifying numbers. You can enter these numbers into the [HP support website](https://www.\\nsupport.hp.com/us-en) for troubleshooting and specifications.\\n\\nThis category contains device pages that can assist with troubleshooting and repair for the following models of HP Pavilion 15 laptop computers:\\n\\n* HP Pavilion 15 cs0xxx\\n* HP Pavilion 15-ab\\n* HP Pavilion 15-au\\n* HP Pavilion 15-au123cl\\n* HP Pavilion 15-aw\\n* HP Pavilion 15-ay041wm\\n* HP Pavilion 15-B\\n* HP Pavilion 15-ba003ds\\n* HP Pavilion 15-ca2073cl\\n* HP Pavilion 15-cc023cl\\n* HP Pavilion 15-cc123cl\\n* HP Pavilion 15-d017cl\\n* HP Pavilion 15-d035dx\\n* HP Pavilion 15-n232nr\\n* HP Pavilion 15-p\\n* HP Pavilion 15-p046nr\\n* HP Pavilion 15-214dx\\n* HP Pavilion 15t\\n* HP Pavilion 15z\\n* HP Pavilion TouchSmart 15\\n* HP Pavilion x360 15-bk152nr\\n\\n## Additional Information\\n\\n[HP Pavilion 15 Official Website](https://store.hp.com/us/en/mdp/pavilion-15-344522--1#!&tab=vao)\\n\\n[HP Pavilion - Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HP_Pavilion_\\\\(computer\\\\))\\n\\n[Why Use a 15 Inch Laptop?](https://www.techradar.com/uk/news/best-15-inch-laptop)\\n\\n### Author\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/Guide/HP+Omen+15-CE0XX+Fan+Replacement/157629\",\n      \"title\": \"HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement - iFixit Repair Guide\",\n      \"publish_date\": \"2024-10-24\",\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"Fix Your Stuff Community Store\\n\\nFree Shipping on Domestic Orders $75+\\n\\n# HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement\\n\\n## Introduction\\n\\nThis guide will walk you through the process of replacing a faulty ventilation fan in your _HP Omen 15-CE0XX_ laptop. A malfunctioning fan can cause overheating and system instability, leading to potential permanent damage to your device. It is important to take appropriate precautions before beginning the fan replacement process to ensure a successful outcome.\\n\\nBefore starting, make sure to _power down_ your laptop completely and _disconnect_ from any external power source. It is recommended to _back up your data_ and review any troubleshooting steps to ensure that the fan is indeed the root cause of the issue.\\n\\nThroughout the process, you will need basic tools such as _screwdrivers_ , _prying tools_ and a _replacement fan_ that is compatible with the _HP Omen 15-CE0XX_ .\\nYou should follow the instructions closely and handle the internal components with care to avoid any damage.\\n\\nOnce you have completed the fan replacement, it is important to test your laptop to ensure that it is running correctly and without overheating. This guide is intended for individuals with basic technical skills, but if you are unsure or not confident in your abilities, it is always best to seek professional assistance\\n\\n## What you need\\n\\n* ## **Step 1** Fan\\n  \\n    + Use a Phillips #0 screwdriver to remove the eight 5.5 mm screws from the bottom cover.\\n    + Use a Phillips #0 screwdriver to remove the two 10 (?) mm screws from the bottom cover.\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\n  \\n  1024\\n  \\n  Cancel Post comment\\n* ## **Step 2**\\n  \\n+ Use a plastic opening tool to gently separate the bottom cover from the main chassis, and pull the cover upwards.\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\n  \\n  1024\\nCancel Post comment\\n* ## **Step 3**\\n  \\n    + Unscrew the four 5.5 mm screws that connect the battery to the main system, and gently detach the battery.\\n    + While removing, make sure to avoid pulling the battery straight out. Instead gently lift the lower half of the battery and slide it away from the motherboard in an away and upwards motion.\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\n  \\n  1024\\n  \\n  Cancel Post comment\\n* \\n* ## **Step 4**\\n  \\n+ Remove the trunk outlet for the replacement fan. This is done by unscrewing the three 5.5mm screws on the trunk outlet and then sliding it outwards to remove.\\n  \\n  Edit\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  Add a comment\\n  \\n  #### Add Comment\\n  \\n  1024\\n  \\n  Cancel Post comment\\n* ## **Step 5**\\n  \\n    + Use a Phillips #00 screwdriver to unscrew the five 5.5 mm screws that secure the bracket to the frame.\\n    + After all screws are loose, gently lift the bracket upwards.\\n\\n...\\n\\ncom/Guide/embed/157629\\\" width=\\\"800\\\" height=\\\"584\\\" allowfullscreen frameborder=\\\"0\\\"></iframe>\\n\\n### Preview\\n\\n**View Statistics:**\\n\\nPast 24 Hours: 1\\n\\nPast 7 Days: 15\\n\\nPast 30 Days: 86\\n\\nAll Time: 2,964\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"url\": \"https://www.userbenchmark.com/System/HP-OMEN-by-HP-Laptop-15-ce0xx/59252\",\n      \"title\": \"HP OMEN by HP Laptop 15-ce0xx Compatible Components\",\n      \"publish_date\": null,\n      \"excerpts\": [\n        \"HP OMEN by HP Laptop 15-ce0xx Compatible Components\\nOMEN by HP Laptop 15-ce0xx Compatible Components (from 3,884 PCs) CPU Core i7-7700HQIntelBench samples 2,776x Core i5-7300HQ GPU HD Graphics 630IntelBench 468x\"\n      ]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"warnings\": null,\n  \"usage\": [\n    {\n      \"name\": \"sku_search\",\n      \"count\": 1\n    }\n  ],\n  \"session_id\": \"ses_0d4353dbfffetaEyYriMe0RXin\"\n}",
