      "code": "{\"url\": \"https://www.ifixit.com/Guide/HP+Omen+15-CE0XX+Fan+Replacement/157629\", \"format\": \"markdown\"}",
      "output": "         HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement - iFixit Repair Guide                                   \n\n           \n\n           \n\n                          \n\n   \n\n  [Skip to main content](#content)\n\n[](/)\n\n[Fix Your Stuff](/Guide)\n\n[\n\nRepair Guides\n\nLearn how to fix just about anything with our step-by-step guides.\n\n](/Guide)[\n\nApp\n\nYour pocket repair helper.\n\n](https://www.ifixit.com/en-gb/go/app)[\n\nFixBot\n\nThe friendly AI repair assistant.\n\n](https://www.ifixit.com/en-gb/go/fixbot)[\n\nRepairability\n\nLearn why fixable products make sense.\n\n](/repairability)[\n\nTeardowns\n\nGet a sneak peek inside the latest gadgets.\n\n](/Teardown)\n\n[Community](/Community)\n\n[\n\nAnswers Forum\n\nShare solutions and get help from a friend.\n\n](/Answers)[\n\nFind Your Community\n\nFind teams, events, and fellow fixers.\n\n](/Community)[\n\nHelp Out\n\nHelp make repair knowledge free and accessible for everyone.\n\n](/Participate)[\n\nRight to Repair\n\nLearn about the Right to Repair movement and how to be an advocate.\n\n](/Right-to-Repair)\n\n[Store](https://www.ifixit.com/en-gb/Store)\n\n[\n\nFeatured\n\nQuality parts and tools backed by our lifetime guarantee.\n\n](https://www.ifixit.com/en-gb/Store)[\n\nTools\n\nShop our wide selection of precision tools.\n\n](https://www.ifixit.com/en-gb/Tools)[\n\nParts\n\nShop parts backed by our quality guarantee.\n\n](https://www.ifixit.com/en-gb/Parts)[\n\niPhone Batteries\n\nBatteries tested and guaranteed plus a kit with everything you need.\n\n](https://www.ifixit.com/en-gb/Parts/iPhone/Batteries)\n\nFree delivery on orders over £65\\*\n\n# HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement\n\n## Introduction\n\nThis guide will walk you through the process of replacing a faulty ventilation fan in your *HP Omen 15-CE0XX* laptop. A malfunctioning fan can cause overheating and system instability, leading to potential permanent damage to your device. It is important to take appropriate precautions before beginning the fan replacement process to ensure a successful outcome.\n\nBefore starting, make sure to *power down* your laptop completely and *disconnect* from any external power source. It is recommended to *back up your data* and review any troubleshooting steps to ensure that the fan is indeed the root cause of the issue.\n\nThroughout the process, you will need basic tools such as *screwdrivers*, *prying tools* and a *replacement fan* that is compatible with the *HP Omen 15-CE0XX*. You should follow the instructions closely and handle the internal components with care to avoid any damage.\n\nOnce you have completed the fan replacement, it is important to test your laptop to ensure that it is running correctly and without overheating. This guide is intended for individuals with basic technical skills, but if you are unsure or not confident in your abilities, it is always best to seek professional assistance\n\n## What you need\n\n  \n\n  -     \n    \n    ## [**Step 1** Fan](#s329563)\n    \n    ![HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement, Fan: step 1, image 1 of 1](https://guide-images.cdn.ifixit.com/igi/ZJOaegptAdVTgmIV.medium)\n    \n    -   Use a Phillips #0 screwdriver to remove the eight 5.5 mm screws from the bottom cover.\n        \n    -   Use a Phillips #0 screwdriver to remove the two 10 (?) mm screws from the bottom cover.\n        \n    \n    [Edit](/Guide/edit/157629/329563)\n    \n     [![](https://assets.cdn.ifixit.com/static/images/answers/answers-fixbot-icon.svg) Ask FixBot](/Join?source=fixbot&last_page=https%3A%2F%2Ffixbot.ifixit.com%2F%3Ftype%3Dguide%26id%3D157629%26stepid%3D329563) Add a comment\n    \n    Add a comment\n    \n    #### Add Comment\n    \n     \n    \n    1024\n    \n    Cancel Post comment\n    \n-     \n    \n    ## [**Step 2**](#s329564)\n    \n    ![HP Omen 15-CE0XX Fan Replacement: step 2, image 1 of 2](https://guide-images.cdn.ifixit.com/igi/sJXKWFUmhbCgc6Ft.medium) \n    \n    ![](https://guide-images.cdn.ifixit.com/igi/sJXKWFUmhbCgc6Ft.200x150)\n    \n    ![](https://guide-images.cdn.ifixit.com/igi/YSDTVEtLjMGJQxqC.200x150)\n    \n    -   Use a plastic opening tool to gently separate the bottom cover from the main chassis, and pull the cover upwards.\n        \n    \n    [Edit](/Guide/edit/157629/329564)\n    \n     [![](https://assets.cdn.ifixit.com/static/images/answers/answers-fixbot-icon.svg) Ask FixBot](/Join?source=fixbot&last_page=https%3A%2F%2Ffixbot.ifixit.com%2F%3Ftype%3Dguide%26id%3D157629%26stepid%3D329564) Add a comment\n    \n    Add a comment\n    \n    #### Add Comment\n    \n     \n    \n    1024\n    \n    Cancel Post comment\n    \n-     \n    \n    ## [**Step 3**](#s329565)\n    \n     \n    \n    -   Unscrew the four 5.5 mm screws that connect the battery to the main system, and gently detach the battery.\n        \n    -   While removing, make sure to avoid pulling the battery straight out. Instead gently lift the lower half of the battery and slide it away from the motherboard in an away and upwards motion.\n        \n    \n    [Edit](/Guide/edit/157629/329565)\n    \n     [![](https://assets.cdn.ifixit.com/static/images/answers/answers-fixbot-icon.svg) Ask FixBot](/Join?source=fixbot&last_page=https%3A%2F%2Ffixbot.ifixit.com%2F%3Ftype%3Dguide%26id%3D157629%26stepid%3D329565) Add a comment\n    \n    Add a comment\n    \n    #### Add Comment\n    \n     \n    \n    1024\n    \n    Cancel Post comment\n    \n-   \n-     \n    \n    ## [**Step 4**](#s329566)\n    \n     \n    \n    -   Remove the trunk outlet for the replacement fan. This is done by unscrewing the three 5.5mm screws on the trunk outlet and then sliding it outwards to remove.\n        \n    \n    [Edit](/Guide/edit/157629/329566)\n    \n     [![](https://assets.cdn.ifixit.com/static/images/answers/answers-fixbot-icon.svg) Ask FixBot](/Join?source=fixbot&last_page=https%3A%2F%2Ffixbot.ifixit.com%2F%3Ftype%3Dguide%26id%3D157629%26stepid%3D329566) Add a comment\n    \n    Add a comment\n    \n    #### Add Comment\n    \n     \n    \n    1024\n    \n    Cancel Post comment\n    \n-     \n    \n    ## [**Step 5**](#s329567)\n    \n     \n    \n    -   Use a Phillips #00 screwdriver to unscrew the five 5.5 mm screws that secure the bracket to the frame.\n        \n    -   After all screws are loose, gently lift the bracket upwards.\n        \n    -   Be careful with the power cable sitting right under this bracket. You might have to move the cable around gently to get the bracket out\n        \n    \n    [Edit](/Guide/edit/157629/329567)\n    \n     [![](https://assets.cdn.ifixit.com/static/images/answers/answers-fixbot-icon.svg) Ask FixBot](/Join?source=fixbot&last_page=https%3A%2F%2Ffixbot.ifixit.com%2F%3Ftype%3Dguide%26id%3D157629%26stepid%3D329567) Add a comment\n    \n    Add a comment\n    \n    #### Add Comment\n    \n     \n    \n    1024\n    \n    Cancel Post comment\n    \n-     \n    \n    ## [**Step 6**](#s329568)\n    \n    -   Disconnect the fan cable from the motherboard using a plastic opening/ pry tool.\n        \n    -   Do not use too much force while pulling the fan cable as it may break. If required, you may use a secondary plastic opening/pry tool for support.\n        \n    \n    [Edit](/Guide/edit/157629/329568)\n    \n     [![](https://assets.cdn.ifixit.com/static/images/answers/answers-fixbot-icon.svg) Ask FixBot](/Join?source=fixbot&last_page=https%3A%2F%2Ffixbot.ifixit.com%2F%3Ftype%3Dguide%26id%3D157629%26stepid%3D329568) Add a comment\n    \n    Add a comment\n    \n    #### Add Comment\n    \n     \n    \n    1024\n    \n    Cancel Post comment\n    \n-     \n    \n    ## [**Step 7**](#s329569)\n    \n    -   Carefully pull the fan out, clean the dust if required.\n        \n    -   Finally, you can now replace the faulty fan with the new fan by following the above steps in reverse order.\n        \n    \n    [Edit](/Guide/edit/157629/329569)\n    \n     [![](https://assets.cdn.ifixit.com/static/images/answers/answers-fixbot-icon.svg) Ask FixBot](/Join?source=fixbot&last_page=https%3A%2F%2Ffixbot.ifixit.com%2F%3Ftype%3Dguide%26id%3D157629%26stepid%3D329569) Add a comment\n    \n    Add a comment\n    \n    #### Add Comment\n    \n     \n    \n    1024\n    \n    Cancel Post comment\n    \n\nConclusion\n\nTo reassemble your device, follow these instructions in reverse order.\n\nGive the author +30 points! You're Finished!\n\n[Cancel: I did not complete this guide.](#)\n\nOne other person completed this guide.\n\n### [Author](#author)\n\nwith [4 other contributors](/Guide/history/157629)\n\n[![](https://guide-images.cdn.ifixit.com/igi/WlYYdGgVbSxgt6LV.standard)](/User/4257210/Nadim+Patel)\n\n#### [Nadim Patel](/User/4257210/Nadim+Patel)\n\nMember since: 01/27/23\n\n154 Reputation\n\n1 Guide authored\n\n[Badges: 4](/User/Graph/4257210/Nadim+Patel)\n\n-   [\n    \n    ](/Badge/Author \"Publish your first guide\")\n-   [\n    \n    ](/Badge/Fixer \"Someone fixed something using your guide\")\n-   [\n    \n    ](/Badge/Initiator \"Start a guide that gets one hundred views\")\n\n[+1 more badge](/User/Graph/4257210/Nadim+Patel)\n\n### 0 Guide Comments\n\nAdd a comment\n\n#### Add Comment\n\n \n\n1024\n\nCancel Post comment\n\n### Embed this guide\n\nChoose a size and copy the code below to embed this guide as a small widget on your site / forum.\n\nSingle Step Full Guide\n\nSmall - 600px Medium - 800px Large - 1200px\n\n<iframe id=\"dozuki-embed-157629\" src=\"https://www.ifixit.com/Guide/embed/157629/full\" width=\"800\" allowfullscreen frameborder=\"0\"></iframe> <script>window.addEventListener(\"message\",function(a){var b=document.getElementById(\"dozuki-embed-157629\"),c=a.data\\[0\\],d=a.data\\[1\\];switch(c){case\"setHeight\":b.style.height=d+\"px\"}},!1);</script> <iframe src=\"https://www.ifixit.com/Guide/embed/157629\" width=\"800\" height=\"584\" allowfullscreen frameborder=\"0\"></iframe> \n\n### Preview\n\n**View Statistics:**\n\nPast 24 Hours: 3\n\nPast 7 Days: 38\n\nPast 30 Days: 125\n